"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.5.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.5.6</span> 标题：腰带（sash, cloth belt）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：אַבְנֵט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：’avnet)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4\">EXO 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:39\">EXO 28:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:40\">EXO 28:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:29\">EXO 39:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:13\">LEV 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:4\">LEV 16:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：חגר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：chagar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:13\">LEV 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:4\">LEV 16:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>腰带是一条长布带，大祭司把它围着腰部缠绕几圈，以扎紧内袍（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.2 内袍、束腰长衬衫、衬衫 (tunic, shirt)&lt;REALIA:4.5.2&gt;</a> ）。其他祭司也束腰带。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:29\">EXO 39:29</a> 记载，大祭司的腰带是用四种线以刺绣的手艺做成的。根据后圣经时期的犹太传统，腰带长32肘（约16米或53英尺）。即使这个传统说法有所夸大，腰带的长度也应该足以缠绕腰部几圈，然后打结扎紧。参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.4 以弗得 (ephod)&lt;REALIA:4.5.4&gt;</a> 中的插图。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 把大祭司系的这条腰带译作“girdle”（“妇女紧身褡”、“腰带”），在现代英文中，这个词可能会误导读者。这条带有刺绣的长腰带除了缠在腰部这个基本用途之外，似乎还有一个象征意义，就是标志着祭司的身份。许多英文译本使用了“sash”（“腰带”）一词，但一些语言可能需要译作“宽带子”。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a> ，要注意区分这条腰带与这节经文稍后提到的“巧工织的以弗得带子”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直译；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直译为“精织的腰带”；参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.4 以弗得 (ephod)&lt;REALIA:4.5.4&gt;</a> ）。</p>\n<p>另参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.6 腰带、皮带 (waistband, sash, belt)&lt;REALIA:6.6&gt;</a> 中的讨论。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
